# Commit and Push Policy

## When to Commit
- A logical unit is complete (feature, fix, refactor, test, or docs).
- The working change grows large; split into small cohesive commits.
- A session log is saved.

## Pre-Commit Checks
- Run tests and linter; do not commit on failure.
- Keep each commit single-purpose and self-contained.

## Commit Message Format (English, Conventional Commits)
- `feat: ...` new feature
- `fix: ...` bug fix
- `refactor: ...` no behavior change
- `test: ...` tests only
- `docs: ...` docs only
- `chore: ...` tooling/config
- Subject: imperative mood, <= 72 chars. Body explains the why, not the what.

## Push Policy
- Auto local commits are allowed.
- Never push to remote without explicit user confirmation (commit-only policy).
- Never force-push or push to `main` without explicit request.

## Safety
- Do not commit secrets (`.env`, credentials).
- Do not amend or rewrite already-pushed history.
